id: pm-arax
title: Fix Windows npm command resolution for extension package installs
description: "Nightly Validation on 2026-05-30 failed only on windows-latest Node 20 because extension install paths that run npm pack/install could not spawn npm (spawn npm ENOENT). Duplicate check: pm context, pm search, list-open, and list-in-progress found no open item specific to Windows npm command resolution; this is a child of pm-59gj because it affects package-first extension install dogfood."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags: []
created_at: "2026-05-30T07:07:36.147Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-30T07:21:05.474Z"
author: maintainer-agent
parent: pm-59gj
resolution: Use platform-aware npm executable selection for extension package installs.
expected_result: Windows and Unix extension package installs can run npm pack/install from pm without spawn ENOENT.
actual_result: "Windows now resolves npm commands to npm.cmd and uses shell mode on win32 for execFile compatibility. Review follow-up linked test run passed: secret scan, 130 focused extension tests, static quality, and typecheck."
comments[4]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-30T07:08:48.060Z",maintainer-agent,"Implementation note: centralized npm executable selection so Windows extension package installs run npm.cmd instead of bare npm, matching the existing Windows test helper behavior and avoiding spawn npm ENOENT."
  "2026-05-30T07:10:39.189Z",maintainer-agent,"Evidence: linked test run passed: secret scan, focused extension unit/integration tests (130 tests), static quality gate, and typecheck. git diff --check also passed. Root cause was bare npm executable resolution on Windows; fix selects npm.cmd on win32."
  "2026-05-30T07:19:31.274Z",maintainer-agent,"Review follow-up: Gemini correctly noted that Windows .cmd npm invocation through execFile needs shell mode. Added shouldRunNpmCommandInShell() and wired runNpmCommand to use shell on win32 with unit coverage."
  "2026-05-30T07:21:03.672Z",maintainer-agent,"Evidence after review follow-up: linked test run passed again after enabling shell mode on win32 for npm.cmd. The rerun covered secret scan, focused extension unit/integration tests (130 tests), static quality, and typecheck."
